293
00:14:12,527 --> 00:14:14,849
And this is the potential for harm to be done to the player.

294
00:14:14,849 --> 00:14:17,991
So more enemies means more threat.

295
00:14:17,991 --> 00:14:21,473
The tougher the enemies are, the more threat.

296
00:14:21,473 --> 00:14:24,615
And the closer the enemies are, the more threat.

297
00:14:24,615 --> 00:14:28,357
Now, players have a certain amount of resources

298
00:14:28,357 --> 00:14:29,858
that they use to handle threat.

299
00:14:30,717 --> 00:14:33,778
You've got defensive resources, and these are health and shields.

300
00:14:33,778 --> 00:14:40,860
And then you've also got offensive resources, which is your ammo, your magic power level.

301
00:14:40,860 --> 00:14:45,641
And so resources can be spent to overcome threat.

302
00:14:45,641 --> 00:14:54,123
So losing health when the player gets shot is effectively spending defensive resources.

303
00:14:54,123 --> 00:14:58,904
Spending ammo to shoot back is effectively spending offensive resources.

304
00:14:58,904 --> 00:15:00,405
And now we have a measure of intensity.

305
00:15:02,128 --> 00:15:05,430
So if the player is reducing threat

306
00:15:05,430 --> 00:15:08,332
by only a small loss of resources,

307
00:15:08,332 --> 00:15:10,133
then the encounter is a little bit too easy.

308
00:15:10,133 --> 00:15:12,235
It's not challenging enough.

309
00:15:12,235 --> 00:15:14,316
However, if lots of resources are being spent

310
00:15:14,316 --> 00:15:15,937
to overcome that threat,

311
00:15:15,937 --> 00:15:17,938
then that means that that encounter is quite hard

312
00:15:17,938 --> 00:15:20,400
and challenging and more intense encounter.

313
00:15:20,400 --> 00:15:23,242
